'''Ian Miller''' (born 13 May 1955) is a former [[Australian people|Australian]] [[Football (soccer)|footballer]] who played his football in [[England]].

==Playing career==
Miller played for [[Bury F.C.|Bury]], [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]], [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]], [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] and [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]]- where he was a member of the side that won the [[Full Members Cup]] in 1987. He joined [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] in June 1989. He began the [[1989-90 in English football|1989-90 season]] as a regular, but lost his place by December 1989 and was released in August 1990. He moved on to [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]] and later [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]].

==Coaching career==
Miller remained active in the game after retiring as a player. He returned to Port Vale as the Community Programme leader in August 1991 and became the youth development officer in May 1992. In November 1994 he left the Vale to become the reserve team coach at [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Kent|first=Jeff|title=Port Vale Personalities|publisher=Witan Books|page=199|date=1996|isbn=0952915200|url=http://www.amazon.ca/Port-Vale-Personalities-Jeff-Kent/dp/0952915200}}</ref> He later coached at Blackburn before joining the staff at [[Leeds United A.F.C.|Leeds United]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/page/LatestNewsDetail/0,,10273~1499466,00.html|title=Boss appoints his first member of coaching staff...|date=27 Dec 2008|work=leedsunited.com|accessdate=2009-03-11}}</ref>

